ctural weakness (freemium/paid tier verification gap, multi-tenant infrastructure) was structural, not just a single CVE; closing one entry point doesn't guarantee no others exist\n- The scale of exposure (275M users) makes Instructure a high-value target indefinitely\n- Forensic investigation was described as \"ongoing\" as of mid-May \u2014 incomplete remediation is a risk\n- The threshold for YES is relatively low (10,000 users, or 100 institutions for 4 hours)\n\n*Factors pushing toward NO (lower probability):*\n- As of July 1-2, no major incidents reported \u2014 ~7 weeks of quiet post-settlement\n- Free-for-Teacher discontinued \u2014 closes the known primary attack vector\n- Enhanced security measures announced; FBI/CISA/DoE oversight creates external accountability pressure\n- ShinyHunters got paid \u2014 may have moved on\n- Only ~58 days remain until resolution, limiting the window\n- Massive reputational, legal, and financial pressure on Instructure to actually fix problems this time\n\n(g) **Change from original 38% forecast:** The research confirms ~7 weeks of quiet since the May 11 settlement, which is modestly reassuring. The closure of Free-for-Teacher removes one confirmed attack vector. However, the fundamental risk factors remain \u2014 ShinyHunters is still active, the ransom payment was a green light to other actors, and the infrastructure serves an enormous user base. The quiet period pulls the estimate slightly downward from 38%, but not dramatically. I'll adjust to approximately 30-33%.\n\n(h) **Community prediction divergence:** The previous forecast was 38%. Given the ~7 weeks of quiet since resolution and the closure of the known attack vector, a slight downward adjustment seems warranted, but I don't have a current community prediction to compare against. My estimate of ~30-32% reflects the reduced (but still meaningful) risk with ~58 days remaining and a relatively low resolution threshold.\n\nBalancing all factors: ~58 days is a meaningful window; the low data exfiltration threshold (10,000 users) makes YES easier to trigger; but the post-settlement quiet period and closed vulnerability are real mitigating factors. I'll settle at **31%**.\n\nProbability: 31%",
